  "original_title": "\u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dba\u0db9\u0dbd\u0dcf\u0dab\u0dca\u0da9\u0dd4\u0dc0 \u0dbb\u0ddc\u0dca\u0dc4\u0dbd\u0dad\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0dc3\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Siyambalanduwa hospital also closed",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "A hospital spokesman said that the Siyambalanduwa Base Hospital was closed due to a shortage of fuel.",
        "The spokesman said that although the hospital staff who are engaged in essential services have been given priority to obtain fuel from petrol stations, the main reason for this is that the doctors are unable to report to the staff due to the lack of any formalities.",
        "The pediatrician has been waiting in line for 17 hours to get fuel. There is no way to bring in paramedics. Some doctors have to send fuel on the bus to bring them to work. More than 75% of the hospital staff do not have the fuel they need to report for work.",
        "Even if they go to get fuel in uniform and after verifying their identity, the people near the petrol stations do not give priority or opportunity to do so."
      ],
